# iOS Home Indicator Spacing

The iOS home indicator (the thin pill at the bottom of the screen) must always have **8px of padding below it**, so it sits 8px from the physical bottom of the screen.

Apply this to every screen and tray that renders its own home indicator:

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT — paddingBottom: 8 on the home indicator wrapper
<div style={{ display: "flex", justifyContent: "center", paddingTop: 16, paddingBottom: 8 }}>
  <div style={{ width: 134, height: 5, borderRadius: 100, backgroundColor: "var(--color-fg)" }} />
</div>

// ❌ WRONG — no bottom padding, or padding applied on a parent instead
<div style={{ display: "flex", justifyContent: "center", paddingTop: 16 }}>
  <div style={{ width: 134, height: 5, borderRadius: 100, backgroundColor: "var(--color-fg)" }} />
</div>
```

Files that currently render the home indicator:
- `web/src/prototype-example/screens/cash/DepositInputScreen.tsx`
- `web/src/prototype-example/screens/cash/DepositTray.tsx`
- `web/src/prototype-example/screens/cash/WithdrawTray.tsx`
